Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 of 15 June 1992 concerning specific measures  for the Azores and Madeira with regard to certain agricultural products  (1), as last amended by  Regulation (EC) No 3290/94  (2), and in particular Article 10 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2225/92  (3), as amended by Regulation (EC) No 1741/94  (4),  sets the quantity of hops in the forecast supply balance which qualifies for exemption from customs  duty on import from third countries or for Community aid and the amount thereof; whereas that  quantity and the aid should be established for the period 1 July 1995 to 30 June 1996;
Whereas the security to ensure compliance by operators with their obligations should be fixed;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the  Management Committee for hops,
